This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with semantic segmentation, which is a popular task in computer vision. The use of meta-learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for few-shot learning, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The incorporation of a linear model for pixel classification suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) category. Finally, the use of episodic training could suggest that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
